    <text>
        <body>
            <p>
                <placeName>Memphis</placeName>
                <date>April 5619</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Dear &amp; Rev Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your favor came duly to hand. I am very obliged to you<lb/> for the
                various hints you gave me and will endeavor to profit by them<lb/>
                <sic>Inclosed</sic> four <sic>dollar</sic> for the two prayer books. I have<lb/>
                found here by a gentleman <persName>Mr. Kaufman</persName> two of your bibles<lb/>
                which you sent him some years ago, it is true they do not look<lb/> any more new but
                still, they can be used, send me an order that<lb/> he can deliver them to me and I
                will endeavor to get you money<lb/> for them, they are worth I suppose from 3 till 4
                dollars yet.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have also commission upon one of the <sic>larg</sic> bibles which
                you are<lb/> now publishing—please send me <del>also</del> one copy
                    <persName>Schwarz</persName>, Geography of <placeName>Palestine</placeName><lb/>
                and state me the price, also two other <add>Hebrew</add>, though they are not
                yet<lb/> ordered to me. I have lectured again before the <sic>litterary</sic>
                society<lb/> subject „Temperance among the Israelites” if you wish to publish<lb/>
                it, give me a hint of it in the „Occident” under notice to correspondence</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The reason that we can for the present do not a great deal for<lb/>
                the <sic>occident</sic> is because many have still <hi rend="underline">the
                    Israelite</hi>, and <hi rend="underline">two</hi> of<lb/> course are too much!
                yes the condition of the Israelites in the country<lb/> is still worse than is the
                large cities, the bread we eat is <add>Hebrew</add>.<lb/>
                <sic>for</sic> one thing, it is <sic>sory</sic> we must confess it, are the
                reformers better,<lb/> they support their ministers better, are more polite.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours in faith</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Jacob Peres</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P.S. Do you not <sic>intent</sic> to finish <persName>I. S. Reggio</persName>. I wish
                you would, as I intend<lb/> to have it published as a whole, by your aid.</p>
        </body>
